# Repository boundary

**This repository** (GrooveGraph Next root) is the sole writable source of truth: docs, `.cursor/`, and the **`product/`** Next.js app (research workbench). There is no parallel in-tree `research/` or `prototypes/` package; historical layouts live in **git history** where docs note it.

## Other folders in the workspace

- **`cursor-agent-baseline`** (or any clone of that starter) is **read-only** here: do **not** edit, sync into, or “mirror” GrooveGraph outputs into it from this project. It is a baseline already applied into GrooveGraph; authoritative policy and code live **only** in this repo.

## Rules

- Prefer in-repo docs and code over informal external notes.
- Do not treat any sibling or external GrooveGraph-named tree as authoritative for this repo.
- Writable outputs belong here: policy, agents, rules, skills, `product/`, `docs/`.
- Read-only external references (vendor docs, TypeDB docs, Figma) are fine; do not copy them in as competing “sources of truth” without review.
- TypeDB schema as committed: **`docs/DB-Schema-Export.typeql`** — refresh with **`npm run dump:typedb-schema`** from repo root when the live DB schema changes.
